Your project uses **MSTest v3 (3.8.0)** on net8.0. Here's what affects you:

### Breaking changes in your code

**`[ExpectedException]` removed** (lines 9, 16) — This attribute is gone in v4. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

Same pattern for `Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation`.

### Other breaking changes to be aware of

Even though these don't appear in your current code, you should know:

| Change | Fix |
|---|---|
| `Assert.ThrowsException` removed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` (or `Assert.Throws` for derived types) |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Just use `[ClassCleanup]` with no argument |
| `TestContext.Properties.Contains()` | Use `.ContainsKey()` |
| `[TestMethod("name")]` constructor changed | Use `[TestMethod(DisplayName = "name")]` |
| `Assert.AreEqual` with format args | Use string interpolation |

### Key behavioral changes (no build errors, but watch for)

- **`TreatDiscoveryWarningsAsErrors`** now defaults to `true` — tests with discovery issues will fail
- **`TestCase.Id`** generation changed — Azure DevOps test history may reset
- **Analyzer severities upgraded** — expect new warnings

